Gazprom and Naftogaz's transit talks with the European Commission broke again
Relations between the GTS operator of Ukraine and Gazprom should be based on the requirements of European energy legislation implemented by Ukraine as a member of the Energy Community.

03 Nov 2019, 15:24

The fourth round of "transit" talks between Russia and Gazprom, Ukraine and Naftogaz, brokered by the European Commission on October 28, failed again. Passions are kindled. Obviously, Ukraine and the Russian Federation are hoping for resolving fundamental issues during the meeting in the "Norman format". However, among the key provisions of the common position are the conclusion of a new long-term contract (10-15 years) and the fixing of volumes of transit that will ensure the reliable operation of the Ukrainian gas transmission system (GTS).
About it in the article for DT.UA writes Alla Eremenko. According to her, the contract should be concluded with the new operator of Ukrainian GTS, which from January 1, 2020 will be completely withdrawn from the Naftogaz group. At the same time, relations between the GTS operator of Ukraine and Gazprom should be based on the requirements of the European energy legislation implemented by Ukraine as a member of the Energy Community.
Andriy Kobolev, Chairman of the Board of Naftogaz of Ukraine, said that it is on such principles that Gazprom works with all its counterparties in the European Union. So why not with Ukraine? In his turn, Energy Commissioner Maros Shefchovych said that Gazprom first insists on the Ukrainian side's refusal to win the Stockholm arbitration. However, it does not mind to return to the Ukrainian gas market.
According to DT.UA, Gazprom does not like:
"- in his opinion, the tariffs for gas transportation by the Ukrainian gas transmission system are too high;
- the absence of a GTS operator certified under European rules;
- Yanukovych's three billion dollar debt, which hangs on Naftogaz with a stone;
- NAC's claim to compensate nearly $ 3 billion of those sentenced in Stockholm arbitration;
- the categorical refusal of Naftogaz to shortly extend (for one and a half years) the "transit" contract from January 1, 2020 under the terms of the current agreement on gas transportation across Ukraine to Europe;
"Naftogaz's reluctance to buy Russian gas under a direct contract and in large volumes."
In turn, Naftogaz of Ukraine against:
"- the construction of" Nord Stream-2 "and" Turkish Streams "bypassing Ukraine, which will deprive NAK and Ukraine of about $ 3 billion in profits;
- non-signing by the Russians of the operator agreement;
- Gazprom's write-off of $ 2.2 billion won in Stockholm arbitration at the transit rate (without penalties and penalties);
- Gazprom's categorical reluctance to pay for "Stockholm accounts", at least property;
- linking the volumes of transit of "Gazprom" fuel to the volume of gas purchases for the needs of Ukraine, which Naftogaz has not done since 2014;
- payment of "Yanukovych's debt" of $ 3 billion;
- the Stockholm win count as repayment of "Yanukovych's debt";
- a short-term "transit" contract (as long as it is necessary for Gazprom) under the terms of an existing contract of 2009.
The author points out that it is extremely difficult to find a mutually acceptable compromise with such demands and disagreements if the parties are generally interested in finding one. Of course, as with any bargain, the parties make a maximum of claims, counting as a result on relatively acceptable terms. Moreover, experts say, and not only in Ukraine, it will be problematic for Gazprom to manage at least 30 or better 50-60 billion cubic meters of gas per year without transit through the Ukrainian gas transportation system. After all, "Nord Stream-2" is not completed.
For more information on the negotiations between Gazprom and Naftogaz, read Alla Eremenko's article "You will not shed tears on GTS" in the "Mirror of the Week. Ukraine" weekly.
